Polytoca is a genus of Asian and Papuasian plants in the grass family .
Triphysaria floribunda is a rare species of flowering plant in the broomrape family known by the common name San Francisco owl's - clover .
Percina phoxocephala , the slenderhead darter , is a North American species of freshwater fish in the family Percidae .
Brazoria truncata , common name Rattlesnake flower , is a plant species in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1834 .
Moonia is a genus of Asian and Australian flowering plants in the daisy family .
Amphissa versicolor is a species of small sea snail in the family Columbellidae .
Lithoxus pallidimaculatus is a species of armored catfish endemic to Suriname where it is found in stony rivulets of the Suriname River basin .
Ictiobus , also known as buffalo fish or simply buffalo , is a genus of freshwater fish common in the United States , but also found in Canada , Mexico and Guatemala .
Sclerocactus wrightiae is a rare species of cactus known by the common names Wright 's little barrel cactus and Wright 's fishhook cactus .
Clarkia bottae is a species of wildflower with several common names , including punchbowl godetia , Botta 's clarkia , Botta 's fairyfan , and hill clarkia .
Asymphorodes triaula is a species of gelechioid moth of subfamily Agonoxeninae of the palm moth family ( Agonoxenidae ) , whose taxonomic status is disputed .
Leprocaulon is a genus of lichen .
Ribes acerifolium is a North American species of currant known by the common names mapleleaf currant and maple - leaved currant .
Eriocaulon koernickianum , common names dwarf pipewort or gulf pipewort , is a plant species native to Oklahoma , Arkansas , Georgia and Texas .
Umbrine : any one of several species of sciaenoid food fishes of the genus Umbrina , especially the Mediterranean species ( Umbrina cirrosa ) , which is highly esteemed as a market fish .
Diplulmaris antarctica is a species of jellyfish in the family Ulmaridae .
Cyathocalyx zeylanicus is a plant species within the genus Cyathocalyx of the family Annonaceae .
Aristolochia delavayi is a species of flowering plant in the famiy Aristolochiaceae .
Calliergon is a genus of moss in the Hypnales order .
Brucella inopinata is a species of Gram - negative , non - motile , non - spore - forming coccoid bacterium , first isolated from a breast implant infection site .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Clypeophysalospora latitans .
Phytoecia virgula is a species of beetle from the Lamiinae subfamily .
Cyrtocarcinus truncatus is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae that lives in the waters around Hawaii .
Himantoglossum hircinum , the lizard orchid , is a species of orchid in the genus Himantoglossum found across Europe , from Spain eastwards to the Balkans and in western North Africa .
Alseodaphne garciniicarpa ( incorrectly A. garciniaecarpa ) , is a species of plant in the Lauraceae family .
Stauroglanis gouldingi is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Trichomycteridae , and the only species of the genus Stauroglanis .
Odontomacrurus murrayi , the Roundhead grenadier , is a species of rattail found in the oceans to a depth of 2,500 metres ( 8,200 ft ) .
The Tosenini are a tribe of cicadas .
Melybia thalamita is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Melybia .
Cuthona concinna is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tergipedidae .
Iodotropheus is a small genus of cichlids endemic to Lake Malawi in east Africa .
Taruga eques ( common names : Günther 's whipping frog , montane hour - glass tree - frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Zoochlorella is a genus of green algae comprising one species , Z. parasitica .
Grevillea pachylostyla , commonly known as Buchan River Grevillea , is a shrub species which is endemic to the upper reaches of the Buchan River in the eastern highlands of Victoria , in Australia .
Gryllus bimaculatus is one of many cricket species known as field crickets .
Barchatus cirrhosus is a species of toadfish native to the western Indian Ocean and the Red Sea .
Allothereua is a genus of scutigeromorph centipedes containing 9 species ranging from Central Asia ( Kazakhstan and Nepal ) to the Philippines to Australia , where at least six species are found .
Agnorhiza invenusta ( syn . Wyethia invenusta ) is a species of flowering plant known by the common names Coville 's mule 's ears and rayless mule 's ears .
Brassavola cucullata , common name Daddy long - legs orchid , is a species of orchid native to Mexico ( from Sinaloa and San Luis Potosí south to Chiapas and the Yucatán Peninsula ) , Central America , the West Indies and northern South America ( Colombia , Venezuela , Guyana , Suriname , French Guinea ) .
The Naididae ( formerly known as Tubificidae ) are a family of clitellate oligochaete worms like the sludge worm , Tubifex tubifex .
Puya laxa is a species in the genus Puya .
The genus Xenoperdix ( `` strange partridge '' ) , described only in 1994 , consists of two species of African partridges that are most closely related to Southeast Asian hill partridges .
Mimofalsoropica kaszabi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimofalsoropica .
The Amazonian manatee ( Trichechus inunguis ) is a species of manatee of the order Sirenia .
Rubus defectionis , the Eclipse blackberry , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Yimenosaurus ( meaning `` Yiman reptile '' ) is an extinct genus of plateosaurid sauropodomorph dinosaur that lived in Chine in the Early Jurassic .
Clytra quadripunctata is a species of leaf beetle in the subfamily Cryptocephalinae .
The Pander 's ground jay , grey ground jay or Turkestan ground - jay ( Podoces panderi ) is a species of bird in the crow and jay family , Corvidae .
The Scyphozoa are an exclusively marine class of the phylum Cnidaria , sometimes referred to as the `` true jellyfish '' ( or sea jellies - as they are not , in fact , fish ) .
Suaeda australis , the austral seablite , is a species of plant in the family Amaranthaceae , native to Australia .
Thorius pulmonaris ( common names : lower cerro pigmy salamander , Cerro San Felipe salamander ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Peregrinus maidis , known as the corn planthopper , is a species of insect in the order Hemiptera and the family Delphacidae .
Leymus racemosus is a species of perennial wild rye known by the common name mammoth wild rye .
Brachygastra is a small genus of Neotropical paper wasps , sometimes referred to as honey wasps , and well known as being one of the few types of insects other than various bees that produce and store honey .
Odontostomops normalops , the Undistinguished sabertooth , is a species of sabertooth fish found in the oceanic depth from 400 to 1,000 metres ( 1,300 to 3,300 ft ) .
Galax ( wandplant , wandflower , or beetleweed ) is a genus in the flowering plant family Diapensiaceae , containing a single species , Galax urceolata ( syn . G. rotundifolia , G. aphylla ) .
Antennaria densifolia ( Denseleaf pussytoes ) is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Madia radiata is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names golden madia and showy madia .
Cylindropuntia molesta is a cactus species endemic to Baja California , Mexico , growing to a size of 2 - 8 feet in height x 2 - 5 feet in width .
Aptenodytes ridgeni , also referred to as Ridgen 's penguin , is an extinct species of penguin from the Pliocene of New Zealand .
Actenobius is an extinct genus of beetles in the family Anobiidae .
Simochromis marginatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known from the Ubwari Peninsula .
Atriplex tularensis is an extremely rare species of saltbush known by the common names Bakersfield smallscale , Tulare saltbush , and Tulare orach .
Cupuliferae is a botanical name : in this case it is a descriptive botanical name : under the ICBN it may only be applied to a taxon at a rank above that of family .
Emerita rathbunae is a species of `` mole crabs '' or `` sand crabs '' in the genus Emerita that lives along the tropical Pacific coasts of the Americas .
Truncatellina atomus is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial animal pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae .
Epinephelus ongus , commonly called White - streaked grouper or Specklefin grouper among various other vernacular names , is a species of marine fish in the family Serranidae .
Chrysopilus is common , worldwide genus of predatory snipe flies .
Indigofera australis , known as Australian Indigo , is an attractive species of leguminous shrub in the genus Indigofera ( Fabaceae family ) .
Melicope sororia is a species of plant in the family Rutaceae .
Eriophyes vitis is a mite species in the genus Eriophyes infecting grape leaves .
Pyropelta musaica is a species of small sea snail , a deep - water limpet , a marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pyropeltidae .
Mermithida is an order of nematode worms .
Latrodectus lilianae is a species of widow spider commonly found in Portugal and Spain .
Papaipema birdi , the umbellifer borer , is a species of moth of the Noctuidae family .
Oecomys bicolor , also known as the white - bellied oecomys or bicolored arboreal rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Oecomys of family Cricetidae .
Packera franciscana ( syn . Senecio franciscanus ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name San Francisco Peaks groundsel , or San Francisco Peaks ragwort .
Perissodus eccentricus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known from Zambian waters .
Lagetta lagetto is a species of tree native to several Caribbean islands .
Oryza australiensis is a wild rice species native to northern Australia .
Dendrocephalus is a genus of fairy shrimp found in South and North America .
Goliathus regius , the Royal Goliath beetle , is a species of beetles belonging to the Scarabaeidae family .
Clavelina moluccensis , common name bluebell tunicate , blue bell tunicate , or Blue Sea Squirt is a species of tunicate ( sea squirt ) , in the genus Clavelina ( the `` little bottles '' ) .
Ostracion solorensis is a species of boxfish native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Desmopuntius hexazona , commonly known as the six - banded tiger barb , is a species of cyprinid fish native to Southeast Asia , from the Mekong drainage basin along the Malay Peninsula to Sumatra and Borneo .
Amietia is a genus of frogs in the Pyxicephalidae family , endemic to central and southern Africa .
Sabal is a genus of New World palms , many of the species being known as palmetto , a loanword from Spanish language for Chamaerops humilis ( palmito ) .
Eucharis × grandiflora is a species of flowering plant in the family Amaryllidaceae , native to western Colombia and western Ecuador and widely cultivated as an ornamental in other regions .
Actaea pachypoda ( doll's - eyes , white baneberry ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Actaea , of the family Ranunculaceae , native to eastern North America .
Rubus palmeri is a rare Mexican species of brambles in the rose family .
Aspredo aspredo is the only species of banjo catfish ( order Siluriformes ) in the genus Aspredo .
Sabella spallanzanii is a species of marine polychaete worms in the family Sabellidae .
Hippomane horrida is a plant species in the Euphorbiaceae first described for science in 1929 .
The Carchi Andes toad , Rhaebo colomai , is a species of toad endemic to the western slopes of the Andes in northern Ecuador and southern Colombia .
Commelina zenkeri is a plant species native to tropical Africa .
Plakobranchus ocellatus is a species of sea slug , a sacoglossan , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Plakobranchidae .
Taniwhasaurus ( From the Maori Taniwha , a supernatural , aquatic creature , and the Greek σαυρος/sauros , meaning lizard ) is an extinct genus of mosasaur ( carnivorous marine lizards ) which inhabited New Zealand , Japan and Antarctica .
Arctostaphylos klamathensis , with the common name Klamath manzanita , is a species of manzanita .
Therioherpeton is a genus based on Therioherpeton cargnini , a small cynodont who lived in the Triassic and was collected in Santa Maria , Santa Maria Formation , the Geopark of Paleorrota , Brazil .
Nanorana taihangnica , or the Taihangshan swelled - vented frog , is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Trachycarpus martianus ( also known as Martius ' fan palm ) is a species in the genus Trachycarpus from two distinct populations , one at 1,500 m ( 4,900 ft ) in the Khasia Hills , Meghalaya Province , in northeast India , the other at 2,400 m ( 7,900 ft ) in central northern Nepal .
Zeltnera namophila ( syn . Centaurium namophilum ) , known by the common name spring - loving centaury , is a rare species of flowering plant in the gentian family .
Asymphylomyrmex is an extinct genus of ants in the formicid subfamily Dolichoderinae .
Chortolirion is a genus of perennial plants in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , first described as a genus in 1908 .
Xanthium ( cocklebur ) is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family , native to the Americas and eastern Asia .
Arthrocnemum subterminale ( syn . Salicornia subterminalis ) is a species of flowering plant in the amaranth family known by the common name Parish 's glasswort .
Butea monosperma is a species of Butea native to tropical and sub - tropical parts of the Indian Subcontinent and Southeast Asia , ranging across India , Bangladesh , Nepal , Sri Lanka , Myanmar , Thailand , Laos , Cambodia , Vietnam , Malaysia , and western Indonesia .
Opuntia phaeacantha is a species of prickly pear cactus known by the common names tulip pricklypear and desert prickly pear found across the southwestern United States , lower Great Plains , and northern Mexico .
Melanostoma fasciatum is a species of hoverfly found in New Zealand , where it is common in agricultural fields and gardens .
Chindesaurus ( /ˌtʃɪndɨˈsɔrəs/ CHIN - di - SAWR - əs ) is a genus of herrerasaurid theropod dinosaur that lived approximately 216 million years ago during the latter part of the Triassic Period in what is now the Southwestern United States .
Lysibia nana is a species of secondary hyperparasitic wasps .
It contains only one known species , Simethis mattiazzii , commonly called the Kerry lily .
Penstemon venustus is a species of penstemon known by the common names Venus penstemon and alpine penstemon .
Rafflesia is a genus of parasitic flowering plants .
Cetengraulis mysticetus is a species of anchovy of the family Engraulidae .
Aloe maculata ( synonym Aloe saponaria ; commonly known as the Soap Aloe or Zebra Aloe ) is a Southern African species of aloe .
Bradyrrhoa confiniella is a species of snout moth in the genus Bradyrrhoa .
Secernentea are the main class of nematodes , characterised by numerous caudal papillae and an excretory system possessing lateral canals .
Bleheratherina pierucciae is a species of freshwater silverside endemic to New Caledonia .
Gahnia ( sawsedge , saw - sedge ) is a genus of sedges native to China , Southeast Asia , New Guinea , Australia , New Zealand and a number of Pacific Islands .
Petunia integrifolia , also known as Petunia violacea and as the violet petunia or violetflower petunia , is a species of wild petunia with violet - colored blooms .
Acanthaecites is an extinct cephalopod genus belonging to the ammonoid family Oppeliidae first described by Rollier in 1909 .
Philanthus gloriosus is a species of bee - hunting wasp found west of the 100th meridian in North America , from Medicine Hat , Alberta south across the High Plains and Rocky Mountains to the Mexican states of Chihuahua , Coahuila , Durango , San Luis Potosí , Hidalgo , Mexico City and Puebla .
Camaridium vestitum , called purple tiger orchid , is a species of epiphytic orchids native to Florida , the West Indies and through Latin America from Mexico to Bolivia .
Aiteng ater is a species of sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Aitengidae .
Noripterus ( meaning `` lake wing '' from Mongolian nuur , `` lake '' and Greek pteron , `` wing '' ) is a genus of dsungaripterid pterodactyloid pterosaur from Lower Cretaceous - age Lianmuqin Formation in the Junggar Basin of Xinjiang , China .
Platanthera psycodes , commonly called lesser purple fringed orchid or small purple - fringed orchid , is a species of orchid , genus Platanthera , occurring from eastern Canada ( from Manitoba to Newfoundland ) to the east - central and northeastern United States ( Great Lakes Region , Appalachian Mountains , and New England ) .
Pusillina kazakhstanica is an extinct species of fossil sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Rissoidae .
Myrmecodia is a genus of epiphytic myrmecophytes ( ant plants ) native to Southeast Asia and large islands extending south to Queensland in Australia .
Heterometrus swammerdami holds the record for being the world 's largest scorpion species at 9 inches ( 23 cm ) in length , and it can weigh as much as 56 grams ( 2.0 oz ) .
Euphorbia nutans is a species of euphorb known by the common names eyebane and nodding spurge .
Cactoblastis bucyrus is a species of snout moth in the genus Cactoblastis .
Trichotroea semiflava is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichotroea .
Lithophragma heterophyllum is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name hillside woodland star .
Millettia grandis is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family from South Africa .
Niassodon is an extinct genus of kingoriid dicynodont therapsid known from the Late Permian of Niassa Province , northern Mozambique .
The Burmese hare ( Lepus peguensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Leporidae .
Corydalis micrantha belongs to genus Corydalis which comprises about 300 species .
Microlophus is a genus of Tropidurid lizards native to South America .
Acromantis grandis is a species of praying mantis found in Vietnam and Nepal .
Pyrrocoma apargioides is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name alpineflames .
Arnocrinum is a genus of herbs in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , first described as a genus in 1846 .
Genlisea margaretae is a carnivorous species in the genus Genlisea ( family Lentibulariaceae ) native to areas of Madagascar , Tanzania , and Zambia .
Clinus latipennis , the False Bay klipfish , is a species of clinid fish that occurs in subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean from Table Bay to Cape Agulhas , South Africa .
Typhleotris pauliani is a species of troglobitic sleeper goby endemic to Madagascar , where it is only known from caves in the southwestern portion of the island .
Illaenus tauricornis is a species of trilobites from Russia and Morocco , from the middle Ordovician .
Conasprella rainesae , common name Maze 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Tetrastigma nitens is a species of liana native to rainforests , dry rainforests and gallery forests of tropical and subtropical eastern Australia .
Plantago elongata is a species of plantain known by the common names prairie plantain and slender plantain .
Metroxylon vitiense ( vitiense - originating in Fiji , also known as the Fiji sago palm ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Arecaceae , endemic to the islands of Fiji ( hence its specific name vitiense , `` of Viti '' , meaning Fiji in Fijian ) , Ovalau , and Vanua Levu in Fiji .
Simplexeburia divisa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Simplexeburia .
Styrax tafelbergensis is a species of flowering plant in the genus Styrax and the family Styracaceae .
Pteraster militaris , the wrinkled star , is a species of starfish in the family Pterasteridae .
Streptomyces fenghuangensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from seawater near Sanya in China .
Nebria yunnana is a species of black and orange coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Yunnan , province of China .
Trichomelanauster albomaculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichomelanauster .
Streptomyces haliclonae is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from the sponge Haliclona sp in the Chiba prefecture from the coast of Tateyama City in Japan .
Litaneutria skinneri , common name Skinner 's ground mantis is a species of praying mantis found in Arizona , New Mexico , and Texas .
Eodicynodon is an extinct genus of dicynodont therapsid from the Permian of South Africa .
Hymenothrix wislizeni , the Trans - Pecos thimblehead , is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Allium obtusum is a species of wild onion known by the common name red Sierra onion or subalpine onion .
Microheros is a spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) with only one described species , M. termitophagus , which occurs in Transvaal and Zimbabwe in Southern Africa .
Banksia praemorsa , commonly known as the cut - leaf banksia , is a species of shrub or tree in the plant genus Banksia .
Richeria grandis is a tree species in the family Phyllanthaceae which ranges from the Lesser Antilles to South America .
Melicope christophersenii is a species of plant in the Rutaceae family known by the common name Waianae Range melicope .
Cyrenella elegans is a fungus species in the genus Cyrenella .
Oncorhynchus masou , known as the masu salmon , masu , or the cherry salmon , is a species of salmon found in the Western Pacific Ocean along East Asia , ranging from the Kamchatka , Kuril Islands , Sakhalin , and Primorsky Krai south through Korea , Taiwan , and Japan .
Astragalus purshii is a species of milkvetch known by the common names woollypod milkvetch and Pursh 's milkvetch .
Leopoldinia is a mostly monoecious genus of flowering plant in the palm family from northern South America ( Colombia , Venezuela , northwestern Brazil ) , where they are known as jará palm or pissava palm .
Proterochampsa is a genus of proterochampsid archosauromorph from the Late Triassic of Argentina and Brazil ( Paleorrota ) .
Castilleja exserta ( formerly Orthocarpus purpurascens ) is a species of plant in the genus which includes the Indian paintbrushes .
Peripatidae is a family of velvet worms .
†Leucocharis porphyrocheila was a species of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Orthalicidae .
Festuca duriuscula ( syn . Festuca ovina L. var . duriuscula Macloskie ) is a species of grass , which is an ornamental plant .
Gryllotalpa africana , also known as the African mole cricket , is a relatively small mole cricket species , native to Africa , but local populations exist in Asia , and southern Europe .
Salix schwerinii is a species of willow native to northeastern Asia ( from Kolyma to northeastern China ) .
Coprozercon scopaeus is a species of mite , placed in its own family , Coprocerconidae , in the order Mesostigmata .
Gypsophila paniculata ( baby 's breath ) is a species of flowering plant in the Caryophyllaceae family , native to central and eastern Europe .
Actiosaurus ( meaning `` coast lizard '' ) is an extinct genus of reptile first described by Henri Sauvage in 1883 .
Kalimeris ( or the Kalimeris Asters ) is a genus of plants in the sunflower family .
Carabus exiguus ochotonarum is a bronze - coloured subspecies of ground beetle from Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Gansu , China .
The Spheroid - flowered Catasetum ( Catasetum globiflorum ) is a species of orchid found in Brazil .
Babelomurex finchii , common name Finch 's latiaxis , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Amata huebneri is a species of moth in the genus Amata of the family Arctiidae ( `` wooly bears '' or `` Tiger moths '' ) .
Mycena nidificata is a species of fungus in the Mycenaceae family of the Agaricales .
Cygnodraco mawsoni , Mawson 's dragonfish , is a species of Antarctic dragonfish native to the Southern Ocean around Antarctica .
The Termite - hill Gecko , Hemidactylus lankae , also known as Sri Lanka Leaf - toed Gecko , is a species of gecko endemic to island of Sri Lanka .
Rossia is a genus of bobtail squid encompassing around ten species .
Paracanthopoma parva is a species of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Trichomycteridae .
Acer opalus ( Italian Maple ) is a species of maple native to the hills and mountains of southern and western Europe , from Italy to Spain and north to southern Germany , and also in northwest Africa in Morocco and Algeria .
Helicophanta magnifica , common name the magnificent helicophanta , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropods mollusk in the family Acavidae .
Ceratozamia whitelockiana is a species of plant in the family Zamiaceae .
Desmoncus is a genus of spiny palms native to the Neotropics .
Lupinus , commonly known as lupin or lupine ( North America ) , is a genus of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Campyloneurum phyllitidis , commonly known as the long strap fern , is a species of fern in the Polypodiaceae family .
Cohnella hongkongensis , formerly known as Paenibacillus hongkongensis , is a species in the Cohnella genus of bacteria .
Geophagus is a genus of cichlids that mainly live in South America as far south as Uruguay , but a single species , G. crassilabris is from Panama .
Cyathea delgadii is a widespread species of tree fern native to Costa Rica , Panama , Venezuela , French Guiana , Guyana , Trinidad , Colombia , Ecuador , Peru , Bolivia , Argentina , Paraguay , and Brazil .
Syringa komarowii is a species of lilac native to central China , commonly called nodding lilac .
Gnaphosa jucunda is a ground spider species found in Russia and Ukraine .
Photinus harveyi is a species of firefly native to Jamaica .
Simochromis diagramma is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it prefers murky waters with rock - rubble substrates usually at less than 5 metres ( 16 ft ) and never deeper than 10 metres ( 33 ft ) .
Cychrus is a genus of beetles in the ground beetle family , Carabidae , and includes the following species :
Caulerpa racemosa is a species of green alga , a seaweed in the family Caulerpaceae .
Austrotrachyceras is a genus belonging to the extinct subclass of cephalopods known as ammonites .
Dynomiellini , is a tribe of beach flies in the family of Canacidae .
Agriochoerus is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore of the family Agriochoeridae , endemic to North America .
Ptilometra australis , the passion flower feather star , is a species of crinoid .
Boeckella palustris is a species of copepod that lives in South America .
Ferrissia tenuis is a species of a freshwater snail or limpet , an aquatic gastropod in the family Planorbidae .
Liolaemus bisignatus ( Philippi 's tree iguana ) is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Knorringia is a genus of plants in the family Polygonaceae with a single species in central Asia .
Parablennius sierraensis is a species of combtooth blenny found in the Eastern and Central Atlantic :
Bracovirus is a genus of viruses , in the family Polydnaviridae .
Pantoporia dindinga also known as the Greyline Lascar is a species of nymphalid butterfly found in Asia , where it ranges from Burma to Peninsular Malaysia , Bangka , Borneo and possibly Sumatra .
Aepyornis is a genus of aepyornithid , one of two genera of ratite birds endemic to Madagascar known as elephant birds .
Quercus cedrosensis , the Cedros Island oak , is a species of plant in the Fagaceae family .
Eriogonum caespitosum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name matted buckwheat , or mat buckwheat .
Melica is a genus of perennial grasses known generally as melic or melic grass .
Physa skinneri , common name the glass physa , is a species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Physidae .
Solidago argentinensis is South American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Myoxocephalus jaok or the plain sculpin is a species of marine fish in the family Cottidae .
Discoderopsis nigrovirens is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Discoderopsis .
The cetacean family Monodontidae comprises two unusual whale species , the narwhal , in which the male has a long tusk , and the dorsal fin - lacking , pure white beluga whale .
Gnaphosa rufula is a ground spider species found in Hungary , Russia , Kazakhstan , Lebanon and Israel .
Farcimen tortum is a species of a land snail , terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Megalomastomatidae .
The Henderson petrel ( Pterodroma atrata ) is a ground - nesting species of seabird in the Procellariidae family .
Psilocarphus elatior is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names tall woollyheads , meadow woollyheads and tall woolly - marbles .
Juncus saximontanus is a species of rush known by the common name Rocky Mountain rush .
Pasiphila debiliata , the bilberry pug , is a species of moth of the Geometridae family .
Amblyomma variegatum , commonly known as the tropical bont tick , is a species of tick of the genus Amblyomma endemic to Africa .
Lamprocystis denticulata is a species o of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Euconulidae , the hive snails .
Adocus beatus is an extinct species of aquatic turtles belonging to the family Adocidae .
Zodarion abantense is a spider species found in Portugal and the Azores .
Ochroconis lascauxensis is a species of fungus of the Ascomycota phylum that was officially described in May 2012 .
Cerithiopsidae are a family of very small and minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs or micromollusks in the informal group Ptenoglossa .
Mormodes maculata is a species of orchid endemic to central and southern Mexico .
Ictalurus is a genus of North American freshwater catfishes .
Myrmica ruginodis is a species of ant that lives in northern parts of Europe and Asia .
Tachina calliphon is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Australia .
Sinocoelurus ( meaning `` Chinese hollow tail '' , in reference to location and to relate the new genus to the North American Coelurus ) is a genus of theropod dinosaur from the ?
The snakehead murrel ( Channa striata ) , is a species of snakehead fish .
Fossils from Eodromaeus were first discovered in 1996 by Argentinean paleontologist Ricardo N. Martinez and Earthwatch volunteer Jim Murphy , and it was first believed that the fossils were a new species of Eoraptor .
Agoseris parviflora is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name Steppe agoseris or sagebrush agoseris or false dandelion .
Raukaua anomalus is a species of shrub native to New Zealand .
Araneomorphae ( sometimes referred to as Labidognatha ) is an infraorder of spiders .
Gomphocarpus is a genus of milkweeds first described as a genus in 1810 .
Echinops niveus is a species in the genus Echinops or globe thistles .
Trochoidea elegans is a species of European air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Arboroharamiya is an extinct genus of early mammal ( or possibly a non - mammalian mammaliaform ) from the Middle Jurassic Tiaojishan Formation of Inner Mongolia , China .
The Coiban agouti ( Dasyprocta coibae ) is a species of rodent in the family Dasyproctidae .
Chorrera postica is a species of snout moth in the genus Chorrera .
Tryella graminea , known as the Grass Buzzing Bullet , is species of the genus Tryella .
Erythrolamprus bizona , commonly known as the false coral snake , is a species of colubrid snake , which is endemic to northern South America and Central America .
Carduus tenuiflorus , known variously as slender - flower thistle , sheep thistle , shore thistle , slender thistle , winged plumeless thistle , winged slender thistle , and winged thistle ) is a species of thistle .
Physaria globosa ( syn . Lesquerella globosa ) , is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family commonly known as globe bladderpod , Short 's bladderpod , and Lesquereux 's mustard .
Eremiaphila yemenita is a species of praying mantis found in Yemen .
Glycymeris nummaria is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Glycymerididae , the bittersweet clams .
Renea moutonii s a species of land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Aciculidae .
The genus Pezoporus contains three Australian species : the night parrot ( Pezoporus occidentalis ) and the cryptic ground parrots , the eastern ground parrot ( Pezoporus wallicus ) and the western ground parrot ( Pezoporus flaviventris ) .
Bythinella bavarica is a species of species of very small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Amnicolidae .
Eugenia orites is a species of plant in the family Myrtaceae , the myrtles .
Herminiimonas saxobsidens is a species of ultramicrobacteria .
Incurvariidae is a family of small primitive monotrysian moths in the order Lepidoptera .
The Acrolepiidae are a family of moths known as false diamondback moths .
Artemisia senjavinensis ( arctic wormwood ) is a rare Arctic species of plants in the sunflower family .
Linum puberulum is a species of flax known by the common name plains flax .
Campbell 's mona monkey , also known as Campbell 's guenon and Campbell 's monkey,(Cercopithecus campbelli ) , is a species of primate in the family Cercopithecidae found in the Ivory Coast , Gambia , Ghana , Guinea , Guinea - Bissau , Liberia , Senegal , and Sierra Leone .
Haplochromis erythromaculatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Rwanda where it occurs in Lake Bulera , Lake Ruhondo and their feeder rivers .
Schizothorax kumaonensis or Kumaon snowtrout is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Schizothorax .
Tyrannosaurus ( /tᵻˌrænəˈsɔːrəs/ or /taɪˌrænəˈsɔːrəs/ , meaning `` tyrant lizard '' , from the Ancient Greek tyrannos ( τύραννος ) , `` tyrant '' , and sauros ( σαῦρος ) , `` lizard '' ) is a genus of coelurosaurian theropod dinosaur .
Falcatifolium angustum is a species of conifer in the Podocarpaceae family found only in Malaysia .
Cyathea inquinans is a species of tree fern native to southwestern Sulawesi and possibly the Maluku Islands , where it grows in montane forest at an altitude of 2000 - 2800 m. This plant has an erect trunk that is usually 2 - 4 m tall .
Eurypholis ( meaning `` broad scale '' ) is a genus of prehistoric fish .
Dryotribus mimeticus was a species of beetle in family Curculionidae .
Annona is a genus of flowering plants in the pawpaw / sugar apple family , Annonaceae .
Pristimantis nyctophylax ( common names : Tandapi robber frog , watchful rainfrog ) is a species of frog in the family Craugastoridae .
Metrosideros nervulosa , commonly known as the Mountain Rose , is a species of flowering plant in the family Myrtaceae .
Lobelia columnaris is a species of the Campanulaceae family .
Plantago princeps is a rare species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name ale .
Ozothamnus hookeri , commonly known as kerosene bush , is an aromatic shrub species , endemic to Australia .
Photoblepharon palpebratum , commonly known as the eyelight fish or one - fin flashlightfish , is a species of lanterneye fish from the Indo - Pacific ( except the westernmost part , where replaced by the similar P. steinitzi ) .
Alpinites is a genus belonging to the Discoclymeniinae subfamily , a member of the Goniatitida order .
Typhlops obtusus , commonly known as the slender blind snake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Didierea madagascariensis , commonly known as the Octopus tree , is a species of Didiereaceae endemic to the spiny thickets of southwestern Madagascar .
Cercocarpus douglasii , common name Klamath mountain mahogany , is a plant species native to northern California and southwestern Oregon .
Mirabilis jalapa , the marvel of Peru or four o'clock flower , is the most commonly grown ornamental species of Mirabilis , and is available in a range of colours .
Porcellionides pruinosus is a cosmopolitan woodlouse that is native to Europe , and is suspected to consist of very closely related species .
Gmelina hainanensis is a species of tree in the Lamiaceae family .
Petroscirtes lupus , the Wolf fangbelly , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean .
Nannophrys is a genus of frogs endemic to Sri Lanka .
Two varieties of Viola walteri are distinguished , and are sometimes considered distinct species .
Alopecurus aequalis is a common species of grass known as shortawn foxtail or orange foxtail .
Senecio iscoensis or Aetheolaena senecioidesis is a species of Senecio in the Asteraceae family that is found only in subtropical and tropical dry shrubland in Ecuador .
Taubateia paraiba was a species of catfish from the family Loricariidae .
Acropora dendrum is a species of acroporid coral that was first described by Bassett - Smith in 1890 .
Olios suavis is a spider species found in Cyprus , Israel and Egypt .
The American pillwort , Pilularia americana A. Braun is an unusual species of fern .
Penaeus esculentus ( the brown tiger prawn , tiger prawn or common tiger prawn ) is a species of prawn which is widely fished for consumption around Australia .
Anisopodus macropus is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Bates in 1863 .
Bothrops pradoi is a species of venomous snake in the Viperidae family .
Hymenocrater is a genus of plants from the mint family .
Ilyodon lennoni , the Chacambero splitfin , is a species of splitfin endemic to Mexico .
Anteater is a common name for the four extant mammal species of the suborder Vermilingua ( meaning `` worm tongue '' ) commonly known for eating ants and termites .
The Citharinidae , the lutefishes , are a small family of characiform fish .
Pethia yuensis is a species of cyprinid fish found in rivers in Manipur , India .
The Turkestan cockroach is primarily an outdoor insect , not known as an aggressive indoor pest , unlike some cockroach species such as the German and brown - banded cockroaches , though it will inhabit areas around dwellings where shelter can be found .
Inocybe is a large genus of mushroom - forming fungi .
Neobracea bahamensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Apocynaceae that is endemic to Cuba and several islands in the Bahamas including Andros , New Providence , Cat Island , Great Exuma , Long Cay and Crooked Island .
Cattleya reginae , often known as Laelia reginae or Sophronitis reginae is a species of orchid endemic to the Serra da Caraça mountains in the state of Minas Gerais of Brazil .
Centaurea stoebe is a species of Centaurea found in Northern Italy .
Allium rosenbachianum is a plant species found high in the Himalayas of Pakistan , Afghanistan , Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan and cultivated in many other regions as an ornamental .
Pueraria phaseoloides is a plant species within the pea family ( Fabaceae ) and its subfamily Faboideae .
Trametes is a genus of fungi that is distinguished by a pileate basidiocarp , di- to trimitic hyphal systems , smooth non - dextrinoid spores , and a hymenium usually without true hymenial cystidia .
Amanita bisporigera is a deadly poisonous species of fungus in the Amanitaceae family .
Longitarsus albus is a yellow coloured species of beetle from the Chrysomelidae family that can be found in Algeria , Israel , and Morocco .
Vriesea splendens or flaming sword is a species of flowering plant in the bromeliad family , subfamily Tillandsioideae .
The sand isopod , Chiridotea coeca , is a species of isopod crustacean found in the western Atlantic Ocean , from Nova Scotia to Florida .
Amarinus lacustris is a species of freshwater crab from Australia , New Zealand and nearby islands , where it lives in water of various salinities .
Agonidus cephalotes is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Agonidus .
The Blissidae are a family in the Hemiptera ( true bugs ) , comprising nearly 50 genera and 400 species .
Xanthogramma citrofasciatum is a species of hoverfly found in grasslands from Ireland to western Siberia .
Halichoeres prosopeion , commonly called the twotone wrasse , half - grey wrasse or zig - zag wrasse , is a fish species in the wrasse family native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Erythrinus is a genus of trahiras from tropical South America .
It contains only one species , Belomantis helenae .
Blandfordia grandiflora is a species of flowering plant native to south - eastern Australia .
Fagraea ceilanica is a species of tree in the gentian family growing to a height of 10 meters .
Gonyaulax is a genus of Dinoflagellates with the type species Gonyaulax spinifera ( Claparède et Lachmann ) Diesing .
Anopina dentata is a species of moth from the Tortricidae family .
Paranchus albipes is a species of ground beetles in the Carabidae family .
Lepidostroma is a genus in the family Lepidostromataceae ( the only family within the fungal order Lepidostromatales ) .
Longitarsus linnaei is a species of beetle of the Chrysomelidae family and the subfamily Galerucinae .
Sapium macrocarpum is a species of flowering plant in the family Euphorbiaceae family .
Hegesinus griphus is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Hegesinus of the family Tachinidae .
Eriogonum wrightii is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common names bastardsage and Wright 's buckwheat .
Clermontia lindseyana is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name hillside clermontia .
This species used to belong to the Stylidium graminifolium complex , but the name was conserved for this single species when two others were split from the complex and introduced as new species in 2001 .
Alcantarea benzingii is a species in the genus Alcantarea .
Zeta argillaceum is one of the most common species of potter wasp in South America .
Euxesta conserta is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Euxesta of the family Ulidiidae .
Bulbophyllum gravidum is a species of epiphytic plant in the Orchidaceae family that is found in Equatorial Guinea and Cameroon ( Bioko and Mount Cameroon , respectively ) .
Nucella squamosa , common name the scaly dogwhelk , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Euphorbia tannensis is a species of herb or shrub native to Australia and some Pacific islands .
Lethrinops turneri is a species of cichlid native to Lake Malawi and Lake Malombe .
In taxonomy , Sphaeroplea is a genus of green algae , specifically of the Sphaeropleaceae .
The Hydrogenothermaceae family are bacteria that live in harsh environmental settings .
Nebria psammophila is a species of ground beetle from the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Kashmir , Kazakhstan , Kyrgyzstan , Nepal , Tajikistan , and Uzbekistan .
Since its erection in 1986 , however , the validity of this subfamily designation has been the subject of much debate , although most phylogenetic studies support the notion that the pygmy chameleons of the subfamily Brookesiinae are not a monophyletic group .
Pelliciera rhizophorae , known as the tea mangrove , is a less - common species of mangroves found along the Pacific coast from the Gulf of Nicoya in Costa Rica to the Esmeraldas River in Ecuador , as well as within stands located in Nicaragua , Panama , and Colombia .
Eriophyllum mohavense , also known as the Mojave woolly sunflower or the Barstow woolly sunflower is a rare species of small annual flowering plant in the aster family , found only ( endemic ) in the Mojave Desert of California .
It contains only one known species , Papuechites aambe , native to New Guinea , the Bismarck Archipelago , and the Indonesian Province of Maluku .
Homala integricollis is a species of beetles in the family Tenebrionidae .
Triplophysa aliensis is a species of stone loach in the genus Triplophysa endemic to Tibet .
Callionymus leucopoecilus is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific waters around the Korean Peninsula .
Psammophis is a genus of colubrid snakes currently comprising 34 species found in Africa and Asia .
Mycena kuurkacea is a species of mushroom in the mycenaceae family .
The Danubio robber frog , Strabomantis zygodactylus , is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Bystrowisuchus is an extinct genus of ctenosauriscid pseudosuchian archosaur from the Early Triassic of European Russia .
Monardella antonina is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name San Antonio Hills monardella .
Lamyropsis microcephala is a species of flowering plants in the thistle family .

Schiedea hookeri is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names Hooker 's schiedea and sprawling schiedea .
Paraprionopelta is a genus of ants in the subfamily Amblyoponinae containing the single species Paraprionopelta minima .
Nardoa rosea , the rose sea star , is a species of sea star of the family Ophidiasteridae .
Megacheuma brevipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Megacheuma .
Desmarestia viridis is a species of brown algae found worldwide .
Mimoblennius cirrosus , the Fringed blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Indian ocean .
Columella columella is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the vertigo snails .
Hesperosuchus is an extinct genus of crocodylomorph reptile that contains a single species , Hesperosuchus agilis .
The genus Eublepharis was first described by the British zoologist John Edward Gray in 1827 .
Cemophora coccinea coccinea , commonly known as the Florida scarlet snake , is the nominotypical subspecies of the scarlet snake .
Desmoceratidae is a family belonging to the ammonite subclass .
Tholymis is a small genus of dragonflies .
Quisque is an extinct genus of prehistoric herring that lived during the Upper Miocene subepoch .
Saltasaurinae is a subfamily of titanosaurian sauropods known from the late Cretaceous period of South America , India and Madagascar .
Erysimum cheiranthoides ( treacle - mustard or wormseed wallflower ) is a species of Erysimum native to most of central and northern Europe and northern and central Asia .
The Osmeriformes comprise an order of ray - finned fish that includes the true or freshwater smelts and allies , such as the galaxiids and noodlefishes ; they are also collectively called osmeriforms .
Pachygaster leachii , the yellow - legged black , is a European species of soldier fly .
The prickly brown ray ( Dipturus teevani ) is a species of cartilaginous fish in the family Rajidae .
Galium aristatum , the awned bedstraw , is a plant species in the Rubiaceae , currently ( May 2014 ) accepted as a distinct species .
Geomyersia is a small genus of skinks from the Bismarck Archipelago and Solomon Islands .
Sericocarpus rigidus is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Columbian whitetop aster .
The Desulfovibrionales are an order of Proteobacteria , with four families .
The mountain worm - eating snake , Trachischium monticola , is a species of colubrid snake .
Carabus obsoletus uhligi is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that can be found in Hungary and Romania .
Cyphella is a genus of fungi in the family Cyphellaceae .
Northern D'Orbigny 's slider , Trachemys dorbigni brasiliensis , is a subspecies of D'Orbigny 's slider from Brazil , though validity of this subspecies is disputed .
Neoplanorbis is a genus of small , freshwater , air - breathing snails .
Photinia integrifolia is a species in the family Rosaceae .
Perideridia howellii is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Howell 's yampah .
Annulohypoxylon archeri ( formerly Hypoxylon archeri ) is a saprophytic species of fungi .
Lagerstroemia loudonii ( Thai : เสลา Salao ) is a species of flowering plant in the Lythraceae family .
The Todd 's nightjar ( Setopagis heterura ) is a species of nightjar in the Caprimulgidae family .
Chrysiptera talboti , known commonly as Talbot 's damselfish and Talbot 's demoiselle , is a species of damselfish .
Chrysso is a spider genus that mostly occurs in the Americas and Asia .
Humulus lupulus ( common hop or hop ) is a species of flowering plant in the Cannabaceae family , native to Europe , western Asia and North America .
Formicoxenus provancheri , common name shampoo ant , is a species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Tytthaspis are a genus of ladybird beetles .
The Philippine fairy - bluebird ( Irena cyanogastra ) is a species of bird in the Irenidae family .
Aeopelys is a monotypic genus of lace bugs , found in New Guinea .
Medicago is a genus of flowering plants , commonly known as medick or burclover , in the legume family .
Dermacentor andersoni , commonly known as the Rocky Mountain wood tick , is a species of tick .
Tethya aurantium , the golf ball sponge , or orange puffball sponge , is a species of demosponge belonging to the family Tethyidae .
Sigaloseps is a genus of skinks which inhabit the moist , closed forest of southern New Caledonia .
Mischocyttarus is a very large , primarily Neotropical genus of social wasps with a few species found also in the Nearctic region .
Anacanthobythites is a genus of viviparous brotulas both found in the eastern Indian Ocean .
Oxycera analis , the dark - winged soldier , is a European species of soldier fly .
Pristionchus maxplancki is a species of diplogastrid nematode ( roundworm ) .
Sitticus longipes is a species of jumping spider that can be found in Austria , France , Italy , and Switzerland .
Trachyodynerus is a genus of potter wasps known from Saudi Arabia .
Amphorella producta is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Ferussaciidae .
Pholistoma is a small genus of flowering plants in the borage family known generally as fiestaflowers .
Leclercqia is a genus of early ligulate lycophyte ( clubmoss ) , known as fossils from the Middle Devonian of Australia , North America , Germany , and Belgium .
Ochna integerrima , popularly called the Vietnamese mickey - mouse plant ( Vietnamese : hoa mai , hoàng mai ) , is a tree species ( sometimes shrub ) of the family Ochnaceae .
Layia leucopappa is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Comanche Point tidytips , or Comanche Point layia .
Limnephilus is a genus of caddisflies in the family Limnephilidae .
Scotinotylus clavatus is a species of sheet weaver found in Austria and Switzerland .
Tillandsia simulata , common name Florida airplant or Manatee River airplant , is a plant species endemic to Florida .
Spiny orb - weavers is a common name for Gasteracantha , a genus of spiders .
The Tephritidae are one of two fly families referred to as fruit flies , the other family being Drosophilidae .
Heterodoxa fatuhivae is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Heterodoxa of the family Tephritidae .
The Juruá red howler ( Alouatta juara ) is a species of howler monkey , native to Peru and Brazil .
Caldukia is a genus of sea slugs , or more accurately nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs , in the family Proctonotidae .
Euryscelis suturalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Euryscelis .
Ecphora gardnerae is a species of fossil predatory sea snail , an extinct marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the rock snails .
Muhlenbergia minutissima is a species of grass known by the common name Annual muhly .
Trachelipus planarius is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in Sicily .
Hydrangea scandens is a species of Hydrangea , native to southern Japan .
Podocarpus lawrencei is a species of podocarp native throughout the Australian high country , from southern Tasmania through to the New South Wales highlands .
Fusicoccum quercus is a species of anamorphic fungus in the family Botryosphaeriaceae .
Lathyrus palustris is a species of wild pea known by the common name marsh pea .
Thunbergia erecta is a herbaceous perennial climbing plant species in the genus Thunbergia native to western Africa .
Hyposmocoma is a large and diverse genus of moths with 320 - 350 known species that have adapted to nearly every ecological niche on the Hawaiian Islands .
Acmella pilosa , the hairy spotflower , is a Mesoamerican species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Udamina leprieurii is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Udamina .
Thurovia is a genus of Texan plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Azhdarchidae ( from اژدرها ( Aždarha ) , the Persian word for dragon ) is a family of pterosaurs known primarily from the late Cretaceous Period , though an isolated vertebra apparently from an azhdarchid is known from the early Cretaceous as well ( late Berriasian age , about 140Ma ago ) .
The Georgetown salamander or San Gabriel Springs salamander ( Eurycea naufragia ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Megacephala chacoensis is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Sawada & Wiesner in 1997 .
Procambarus texanus ( the `` Bastrop crayfish '' ) is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Sorbus californica , the California mountain ash , is an aggregate species of Rowans native to western North America and sometimes cultivated .
Haigia nevadana is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Haigia of the family Tephritidae .
Melicope lydgatei is a rare species of flowering plant in the citrus family known by the common names Koolau Range melicope and Lydgate 's pelea .
Ekemblemaria myersi , the Reefsand blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found from the Gulf of California to Colombia , in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Delonix regia is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae , subfamily Caesalpinioideae .
Fissurella picta , common name : the painted keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
The family Jubulaceae ( occasionally Frullaniaceae ) , is a family of liverworts .
Gymnosporangium is a genus of heteroecious plant - pathogenic fungi which alternately infect members of the family Cupressaceae , primarily species in the genus Juniperus ( junipers ) , and members of the family Rosaceae in the subfamily Maloideae ( apples , pears , quinces , shadbush , hawthorns , rowans and their relatives ) .
Carex praeceptorum ( orth.var . C. praeceptorium ) is a species of sedge known by the common names early sedge and teacher 's sedge .
The Pucciniaceae are a family of rust fungi that cause plant diseases , mainly on cereals such as wheat .
Aplidium californicum is a species of colonial sea squirt , a tunicate in the family Polyclinidae .
It consists of only one species , Caraccochylis framea , which is found in Brazil ( Minas Gerias ) .
Spirotropis carinata is a fossil species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Drilliidae .
Astragalus monoensis is a rare species of milkvetch known by the common name Mono milkvetch .
Ralfsiales is an order of crustose brown algae ( class Phaeophyceae ) containing two families .
Pinus nigra , the Austrian pine or black pine , is a moderately variable species of pine , occurring across southern Mediterranean Europe from Spain to the eastern Mediterranean on Anatolian peninsula of Turkey and on Corsica / Cyprus , including Crimea , and in the high mountains of the Maghreb in North Africa .
Potentilla gracilis , known as slender cinquefoil or graceful cinquefoil , is a species of cinquefoil .
Diplodonta punctata , or the Atlantic diplodon , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Ungulinidae .
Peripatoides suteri is a species of peripatus in the Peripatopsidae family .
Raorchestes kadalarensis is a species of frog of the genus Raorchestes found in Kadalar near Munnar in the Western Ghats of Kerala in India .
Marcgravia is a genus of plant in family Marcgraviaceae , native to the Caribbean Islands , Central America , and South America .
Larimichthys is a genus of ray - finned saltwater fishes commonly known as yellow croakers .
Coris batuensis ( Batu coris or Batu rainbow - wrasse ) , is a species of wrasse native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean from the African coast to the Marshall Islands and from southern Japan to Australia 's Great Barrier Reef and Tonga .
Tacua speciosa is a very large Southeast Asian species of cicada .
Trichomonas is a genus of anaerobic protists that are parasites of vertebrates .
Pseudozonaria arabicula , common name : the little Arabian cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Tripteris is a genus of African plants in the pot marigold tribe within the daisy family .
Califortalis hirsutifrons is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Califortalis of the family Ulidiidae .
Isostichopus badionotus , also known as the chocolate chip cucumber or the cookie dough sea cucumber , is a species of sea cucumber in the family Stichopodidae .
Terminalia avicennioides ( Bambara : Wolobugun ) is a tree species in the genus Terminalia found in West Africa .
Mimotetrorea spinipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimotetrorea .
Platyrhinops is an extinct genus amphibamid temnospondyl from the Late Carboniferous ( late Westphalian stage ) of Ohio and the Czech Republic .
Macrobaenetes kelsoensis is a species of insect in family Rhaphidophoridae known commonly as the Kelso giant sand treader cricket .
Caulolatilus is a genus of tilefishes native to the Pacific and Atlantic coasts of the Americas .
Gentiana asclepiadea ( willow gentian ) is a species of flowering plant of the genus Gentiana in the family Gentianaceae , native to central and eastern Europe from primarily mountain ( montane ) woodland though it does occur in less wooded open pasture in some areas , perhaps persisting after woodland clearance .
Philodryas olfersii is a species of colubrid snake , endemic to South America , known by the common names Lichtenstein 's green racer , South American green racer , and eastern green whiptail , and in Brazil , cobra - cipó , cobra de São João , cobra - facão , cobra - verde , and mboi - obi .
Mizuhobaris is an extinct genus of shelled octopods from the Late Miocene .
Nyearctia is a genus of arctiine tussock moths in the Erebidae family .
Scutellastra cochlear is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Patellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Aegolius is a genus of small true owls .
Nicotiana glutinosa is a species of tobacco plant that is economically important in tobacco hybrids .
Rubus nivalis , commonly known as snow raspberry , is a species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Acer davidii ( Père David 's Maple ) , is a species of maple in the snakebark maple group .
Passiflora jamesonii is a species of plant in the Passifloraceae family .
The Hatutu Marquesan warbler ( Acrocephalus percernis postremus ) , also called the Hatutu Polynesian warbler or the long - billed Polynesian warbler , is a subspecies of the northern Marquesan reed warbler .
Dolichopteroides binocularis is a species of barreleye found in oceanic waters at depths of from 960 to 1,200 metres ( 3,150 to 3,940 ft ) .
Pupa affinis is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Acteonidae .
Ophthalmoptera undulata is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Ophthalmoptera of the family Tephritidae .
Sectator ocyurus , the bluestriped chub , is a species of sea chub native to the Pacific coast of the Americas from Baja California to Peru .
Houstonia parviflora ( Greenman 's bluet or few - flowered bluet ) is a plant species in the Rubiaceae , found only in south - central Texas .
Athyrium ( lady - fern ) is a genus of about 180 species of terrestrial ferns , with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Nemophila breviflora is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names basin nemophila , Great Basin nemophila , and Great Basin baby - blue - eyes .
Ernobius mollis is a species of beetles in the genus Ernobius of the family Anobiidae is native to northern Europe .
Melvius is a genus of vidalamiin amiid fish from the Late Cretaceous .
Whiteodendron is a genus of plant in family Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1952 .
Glomerella tucumanensis is a species of fungus in the family Glomerellaceae .
Limnomedusa macroglossa ( common name : rapids frog ) is a species of frog in the Alsodidae family , in the monotypic genus Limnomedusa .
Sympistis deserticola was a species of moth of the Noctuidae family .
Phreatoicidea is a suborder of isopod crustaceans .
Trogolaphysa carpenteri is a species of aquatic springtail that is known from Argentina , Costa Rica , Mexico , and Cayenne , French Guiana .
Philinopsis taronga is a species of small and colorful aglajid sea slug , a shell - less opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Aglajidae .
The Enchanting Dendrobium ( Dendrobium bellatulum ) is a species of orchid .
Hopea chinensis is a species of medium - sized tree ( 15 - -20 metres ( 49 - -66 ft ) tall ) in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Allium prattii is an Asian species of wild onion native to Assam , Nepal , Sikkim , Bhutan , and China ( Anhui , Gansu , Henan , Qinghai , Shaanxi , Sichuan , Tibet , Yunnan ) .
Pyroteuthis margaritifera , the jewel enope squid , is a species of squid in the family Pyroteuthidae .
Yersiniops solitaria is a species of praying mantis native to the United States .
Diamantomyidae is a family of extinct hystricognath rodents from Africa and Asia .
Pachycara is a genus of eelpouts found in Atlantic , Indian , Southern and Pacific Ocean .
The green mountain frog , or Odorrana livida , is a species of frog in the Ranidae family that is endemic to Burma .
Juncus roemerianus is a species of flowering plant in the rush family known by the common names black rush , needlerush , and black needlerush .
Protomelas dejunctus , the Fire Blue Hap , is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from around Chinyankwazi Island and Chinyamwezi Island in the southern portion of the lake .
Zhyraornis is a genus of prehistoric bird from the late Cretaceous period ( middle Turonian , 92 mya ) .
Bibarba bibarba is a species of loach that is found in the Chengjiang River in China .
Limnodynastes dorsalis is a frog species from the family Myobatrachidae .
Johnrandallia nigrirostris , the blacknosed butterflyfish or barberfish ( from the Spanish names , El Barbero or Mariposa Barbero , `` the barber '' or `` butterfly barber '' ) , is a species of fish in the family Chaetodontidae , the butterfly fishes .
Hypopygus neblinae is a species of bluntnose knifefish from the family Hypopomidae .
Jacobaea adonidifolia is a species ( synonym Senecio adonidifolius ) of the genus Jacobaea and the family Asteraceae .
Pannychina atripennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pannychina .
Proctophyllodes is a genus of feather mites , found on passerine birds .
The forest shrews are the members of the genus Sylvisorex .
Melanomys caliginosus , also known as the dusky melanomys or dusky rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Melanomys of family Cricetidae .
Polylepis ( pronounced pah - lee - LEE - piss or pah - lee - LEH - piss ) is a genus comprising twenty eight recognised shrub and tree species , that are endemic to the mid- and high - elevation regions of the tropical Andes .
Uahuka is a genus of linyphiid spiders with two species that occur only on the Marquesas Islands .
The Guatemalan broad - clawed shrew ( Cryptotis griseoventris ) is a species of small - eared shrew in the family Soricidae .
Rehderella belyaevi is an unusual and monotypic barnacle genus restricted to Easter Island and Pitcairn Island .
Melicope degeneri is a rare species of flowering plant in the citrus family known by the common names Kokee Stream melicope and Degener 's pelea .
Krauseia is an extinct genus of small mammal from the Paleocene of North America .
Parapomecyna flavomaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parapomecyna .
Istiblennius flaviumbrinus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian Ocean , specifically the Red Sea .
Perisama bomplandii , the Bomplandi 's Perisama , is a species of butterflies belonging to the family Nymphalidae .
Placetron wosnessenskii , common name the scaled crab , is a species of king crab found in most waters off North America 's west coast .
The Rapateaceae are a family of flowering plants .
Compsocerops is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian that lived during the Late Triassic in what is now India .
Salamandra is a genus of six species of salamanders localized in central and southern Europe , Northern Africa , and western Asia .
Mitra zonata , common name zoned mitre , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miters or miter snails .
Polemon christyi , or the eastern snake - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Colobura is a genus in the Nymphalidae family found from Mexico to South America .
Geissospermum is a genus of flowering plants in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1846 .
Berzelia lanuginosa is a species of flowering plant in the family Bruniaceae .
Pelargonium zonale , known as horse - shoe pelargonium or wildemalva in Africaans , is a wild species of Pelargonium native to southern Africa , belonging to the geranium family , Geraniaceae .
Acacia williamsonii , known colloquially as Whirrakee wattle , is a species of Acacia native to southern New South Wales and Victoria in eastern Australia .
Cirripectes obscurus , the Gargantuan blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny that inhabits coral reefs in the Hawaiian island chain .
Ceanothus confusus is a species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae known by the common name Rincon Ridge ceanothus .
Daemonosaurus was named by Hans - Dieter Sues , Sterling J. Nesbitt , David S. Berman and Amy C. Henrici in the journal Proceedings of the Royal Society B in 2011 and the type species is Daemonosaurus chauliodus .
Claytonia cordifolia is a species of wildflower in the purslane family known by the common name heartleaf springbeauty .
Celerina heffernani , known commonly as the Hefferman 's Starfish , is a species of marine echinoderm in the family Ophidiasteridae .
Zygophyllum fabago is a species of plant known by the common name Syrian bean - caper .
Pseudopusula californiana , common name the `` coffee bean trivia '' , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Triviidae , the trivias .
The Paracryphiaceae are a family of woody shrubs and trees native to Australia , southeast Asia , and New Caledonia .
Cerradomys subflavus , also known as the terraced rice rat or flavescent oryzomys , is a rodent species from South America in the genus Cerradomys .
Calotrophon ostrearum , common name the `` mauve - mouth drill '' , is a species of small , predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Lacuna turneri is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
Platysuchus is an extinct genus of teleosaurid crocodyliform from the Early Jurassic ( Toarcian ) .
Asterolecaniidae is a family of scale insects commonly known as pit scales or asterolecaniids .
The Puerto Rican crested toad or simply Puerto Rican toad ( Peltophryne lemur ) is a species of toad found only in Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands .
The Uraniidae are a family of moths containing four subfamilies , ninety genera , and roughly seven - hundred species .
Acromantis indica , common name Burmese mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Myanmar .
Scleroplax granulata is a species of crab in the monotypic genus Scleroplax .
Aphonopelma anax , commonly known as the Texas tan tarantula , is a species of spider belonging to the family Theraphosidae .
Tetragonitidae is a family of Cretaceous lytoceratin ammonites typically with square or trapezoidal whorl section at least during some growth stage .
Sphaeropleaceae is a family of green algae , in the order Chlorococcales .
Gnathorhiza is an extinct genus of prehistoric lobe - finned fish which lived during the Permian period .
It was described by Kobayashi in 1951 , and the type species is Calymenesum tingi , originally described under the genus Calymene by Sun in 1931 .
Penicillium rubrum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which produces kojic acid , mitorubrin , mitorubrinol , rubratoxin A , rubratoxin B rubralactone , rubramin and occurs in grain corn and soybeans .
The Vilcabamba thistletail ( Asthenes vilcabambae ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Nassauvia serpens ( also called snakeplant ) is a species of plant in the Asteraceae family .
Miriquidica deusta is a species of lichen in the Lecanoraceae family .
The Chorizanthe fimbriata species is endemic to the San Jacinto Mountains ( California ) and the Peninsular Ranges in Southern California and Baja California , below 1,600 metres ( 5,200 ft ) .
Bradburia hirtella is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family , native to Texas and Louisiana in the south - central United States .
Actinomyces georgiae is a species in the genus of Actinomyces .
The Nicobar imperial pigeon ( Ducula nicobarica ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
It was described by Henry in 1968 , and the type species is Guichenia dufouri , which was originally described under the genus Dalmanites by Tromelin and Lebesconte in 1876 .
Abralia renschi is a species of enoploteuthid cephalopod found in the waters of Sumatra , Java and the Maldives .
The Timor bush warbler ( Locustella timorensis ) is a songbird species .
Neocrepidodera basalis is a species of flea beetle from a leaf beetle family that is endemic to Italy .
Pecluma , the rockcap ferns is a genus of fern in family Polypodiaceae .
The Pithraj tree , ( Aphanamixis polystachya ) , is a species of tree in the family Meliaceae .
Mycobacterium intracellulare is a species of the phylum actinobacteria ( Gram - positive bacteria with high guanine and cytosine content , one of the dominant phyla of all bacteria ) , belonging to the genus Mycobacterium .
Heliomeris longifolia is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family called the Longleaf false goldeneye .
Zabrus jurjurae is a species of ground beetle in the Lobozabrus subgenus that is endemic to Algeria .
Tabanus glaucopis also known as the downland horsefly is a species of biting horse - fly .
Euchelus atratus , common name the blackish margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chilodontidae .
Senna hebecarpa , with the common names American senna and wild senna , is a species of legume native to eastern North America .
Erigeron petiolaris is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Marseilleviridae is a family of double stranded DNA viruses .
Xylodromus fleischeri is a species of rove beetle in the Omaliinae subfamily that is endemic to Romania .
It contains only one species , Palmartona catoxantha , which is found from Myanmar eastwards throughout Malaysia , Singapore , Indonesia ( Sumatra , Nias , Java , Bangka , Kalimantan , Sulawesi ) , the Philippines ( Palawan ) to Papua New Guinea .
Pseudocetonurus septifer is a species of rattail , the only known species in the genus Pseudocetonurus .
Laniarius is a genus of brightly coloured , carnivorous passerine birds commonly known as boubous or gonoleks .
Semljicola alticola is a spider species found in Sweden , Finland and Russia .
Brassiantha hedraiantheroides is a species of Australian understory shrubs or small trees , constituting part of the plant family Celastraceae .
Tydeus domesticus is a species of mite belonging to the genus Tydeus .
Sidymella rubrosignata is a species of crab spider found in Australia .
The only species in the genus Barawertornis , its fossil remains are found in strata of the Riversleigh deposits located at two sites in Northwestern Queensland , Australia .

Acacia ashbyae , commonly known as Ashby 's wattle , is a species of wattle that is endemic to Western Australia .
Ivesia callida is a rare species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Tahquitz mousetail .
Ballota acetabulosa , the false dittany or Greek horehound , is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , native to Southeast Greece , Crete , and West Turkey .
Haementeria ghilianii , the giant Amazon leech , is one of the world 's largest species of leeches .
Arbutus occidentalis is a shrub species in the heath family , that is endemic to Mexico .

Encelia nutans , called noddinghead , or nodding sunray , is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Gracixalus nonggangensis is a species of shrub frog from southern Guangxi , China , near the Vietnamese border , and presumably to be also found in adjacent Vietnam .
Cyperales is a name for an order of flowering plants .
Agave bracteosa is a species of agave sometimes known as `` spider agave '' or `` squid agave . ''
Odorrana banaorum is a species of frog in the Ranidae family that is known from Vietnam and Cambodia .

The Micronoctuini are a tribe of moths in the Erebidae family that includes about 400 described species .
Prochetodon is a genus of mammals from the extinct order Multituberculata .
Aponogeton undulatus is a species of aquatic plant , sometimes used in aquariums .

Megaceryle is a genus of very large kingfishers .

Brookesia micra is a species of chameleon from the islet of Nosy Hara in Antsiranana , Madagascar .
Rhododendron wallichii ( 簇毛杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to northeastern India , eastern Nepal , Bhutan , Sikkim , and southern Xizang in China , where it grows at altitudes of 3000 - -4300 meters .
Lasiognathus intermedius is a species of wolftrap angler known from the western Atlantic Ocean and the southeastern Pacific Ocean where it occurs at depths of around 1,265 metres ( 4,150 ft ) .
Lentalius dorsopictus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Lentalius .
Canarium vitiense is a rainforest tree species , of the plant family Burseraceae , growing naturally in Fiji , the Solomon Islands , Samoa , Tonga , New Guinea , Bismarck Archipelago , Admiralty Islands , Louisiade Archipelago , Torres Strait Islands and in lowland north - eastern Queensland , Australia .
Rhopalostylis baueri is a species of palm native to Norfolk Island ( Australia ) and to the Kermadec Islands ( New Zealand ) .
Cyclopides is a genus of skippers .
Rosa cymosa is a species of climbing rose native to China , where it grows from the east coast in Fujian to western Sichuan at up to 1300 m , in warm areas in scrub and gorges , and in bamboo plantations .
Nannoscincus is a genus of small skinks endemic to New Caledonia .
The Cynipoidea are a moderate - sized hymenopteran superfamily that presently includes five modern families and three extinct families , though others have been recognized in the past .
Elephantopus elatus , common name tall elephantsfoot , is a North American species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .

Caladenia lobata , commonly known as the Butterfly orchid is a species of orchid endemic to the south -- west of Western Australia .

Tomentgaurotes plumbeus is a species of beetle in the Thornberry family Cerambycidae .

Pterocactus ( from Greek pteron , `` wing '' , referring to the saucer - shaped seed of these plants ) is a genus of the cactus family ( Cactaceae ) , comprising 9 species .

Suaeda esteroa is a species of flowering plant in the amaranth family known by the common name estuary seablite .
