Distorsio kurzi , common name Kurz 's distorsio , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Personidae , the Distortio snails .
Tritomegas is a genus of shield bugs .
Platostoma palustre , commonly as Chinese mesona , is a species of plants belonging to the genus Platostoma of the mint family .
Conringia is a genus of plants in the mustard family known commonly as hare 's ear mustards .
One of many rare tropical plants in the Costus family , Costus osae is a species native to Costa Rica described in 1997 .
It is monotypic , containing the single species Hypotarzetta insignis .
Leninia was first named by Valentin Fischer , Maxim S. Arkhangelsky , Gleb N. Uspensky , Ilya M. Stenshin and Pascal Godefroit in 2013 and the type species is Leninia stellans .
Falsometopides fuscomaculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Falsometopides .
Creobroter pictipennis , with the common name Indian flower mantis , is a species of praying mantis native to Asia .
Aubria masako ( common name : Masako ball frog ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
Pseudomugil pellucidus , commonly known as the transparent blue - eye , is a species of fish in the family Pseudomugilidae .
Pseudacanthicus spinosus is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Amazon Basin .
Erebus macrops is a species of moth of the family Erebidae .
Lipotriches notiomorpha is a species of bee in the genus Lipotriches , of the family Halictidae .
Aldrovanda vesiculosa , commonly known as the waterwheel plant , is the sole extant species in the flowering plant genus Aldrovanda of the family Droseraceae .
Tanacetum is a genus of about 160 species of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , native to many regions of the Northern Hemisphere .
Nassella viridula is a species of grass known by the common name green needlegrass .
Delomys is a genus of South American rodents in the tribe Thomasomyini of family Cricetidae .
Sitticus floricola is a species of jumping spider that can be found in Scotland and other parts of the United Kingdom .
Festuca vivipara ( viviparous sheep's - fescue ) is a species of grass native to northern Europe , northern Asia , and subarctic North America .
Neocollyris bipartita is a species of ground beetle in the genus Neocollyris in the subfamily of Carabinae .
Andersonia sprengelioides is a species of shrub that grows in the south west corner of Western Australia .
The Phytalmiinae are a subfamily of tephritid fruit flies .
Anredera cordifolia , commonly known as the Madeira - vine or mignonette vine , is a South American species of ornamental succulent vine of the family Basellaceae .
Caylusea abyssinica is a plant species found in East Africa .
Erronea pyriformis , common name the Pear - shaped Cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Veronica cusickii is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name Cusick 's speedwell .
Macropharyngodon is a genus of wrasses native to the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Chama sarda , or the cherry jewel box clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Chamidae .
Acontias percivali , also known as Percival 's legless lizard , Tanzanian legless lizard , and Percival 's lance skink , is a small , legless ( snake - like ) species of lizard in the family Scincidae , collectively known as `` skinks '' .
Nebria xanthacra is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Iran , Turkmenistan , and Himachal Pradesh province of India .
Decanema is a small genus in the dogbane family first described as a genus in 1838 .
Phytomonas is a genus of trypanosomes that infect plants .
Chamaecyparis taiwanensis ( Taiwan Cypress ; simplified Chinese : 台湾扁柏 ; traditional Chinese : 臺灣扁柏 ; pinyin : tái wān biǎn bǎi ) is a species of cypress , native to the mountains of Taiwan , where it grows at altitudes of 1300 - -2800 m.
Psathyrella canadensis is a species of agaric fungus in the family Psathyrellaceae .
Cardamine nuttallii is a species of cardamine known by the common name Nuttall 's toothwort .
Deinandra conjugens ( syn . Hemizonia conjugens ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Otay tarplant and Otay tarweed .
Eutypomyidae is a family of extinct rodents from North America and Eurasia thought to be related to modern beavers .
Cephalanthus salicifolius is a species of flowering plant in the cinchona family , Rubiaceae .
Mimulus johnstonii is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name Johnston 's monkeyflower .
The genus Eumeces ( family Scincidae ) comprises four African to Middle - Eastern skink species .
Neoprocolophon is an extinct genus of procolophonid parareptile , known from the single species Neoprocolophon asiaticus from the Middle Triassic of China .
Hylarana leptoglossa , commonly known as the long - tongued frog , is a species of true frog in the genus Hylarana .
Lasius alienus , or cornfield ant , is a species of ant in the subfamily Formicinae ( family Formicidae ) .
Cyamopsis is a genus of the family Fabaceae .
The Taiwan bush warbler ( Locustella alishanensis ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Locustellidae family .
Erythrinus kessleri is a species of trahira ( family Erythrinidae ) .
Echinopogon is a genus of grasses native to Australia , New Guinea , Indonesia , and New Zealand .
Hyphodontia aspera is a species of fungus in the family Schizoporaceae .
Graphium empedovana is a species of butterfly of the family Papilionidae , that is found in the Philippines ( Balabac , Busuanga , Palawan ) .
Acrossocheilus xamensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Acrossocheilus .
The liocichlas are a group of birds in the genus of the same name , Liocichla , from the Leiothrichidae family .
Laudakia dayana , commonly known as the Haridwar agama , is a species of agamid lizard found in Haridwar , India .
Bohaskaia is an extinct genus of beluga - like odontocete cetacean known from the Early Pliocene of Virginia and North Carolina , USA .
The Nagtglas 's African dormouse ( Graphiurus nagtglasii ) is a species of rodent in the family Gliridae .
Amorphoscelis annulicornis is a species of praying mantis found in Sri Lanka , India , Nepal , and Malaysia .
Rhododendron yunnanense ( 云南杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to Myanmar and Guizhou , Shaanxi , Sichuan , Xizang , and Yunnan , China , where it grows at altitudes of 2200 - -3600 meters .
Chaerilus ceylonensis is a species of scorpion in Chaerilidae family .
Parepicedia fimbriata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parepicedia .
Crinum thaianum , Common name Thai Onion plant or Water onion , is an emergent plant species endemic to coastal plain of southern Thailand in Ranong and Phang Nga Provinces .
Heliodorus cochisensis is a Nearctic species of tachinid flies in the genus Heliodorus of the family Tachinidae .
Asclepias verticillata ( whorled milkweed , eastern whorled milkweed , horsetail milkweed ) is a species of milkweed native to most all of eastern North America and parts of western Canada and the United States .
Dillwynia laxiflora is a shrub species in the pea family .
Catophractes alexandri , the only species in the genus Catophractes , is a spiny shrub or small tree up to 3 m tall , belonging to the family Bignoniaceae and occurring in the hot , low - rainfall regions of Namibia , the Northern Cape , Kalahari Desert , Botswana , western Zimbabwe and the Northern Transvaal .
Pennisetum villosum is a species of grass known by the common name feathertop grass .
Milbert 's Tortoiseshell ( Aglais milberti ) , also known as the Fire - rim Tortoiseshell , is the only species of Aglais that occurs in North America .
Draba cruciata is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known as the Mineral King draba .
Oxycera nigricornis , the delicate soldier , is a European species of soldier fly .
Proterix is an extinct genus of insectivore from the Late Oligocene to the Early Miocene of North America .
Alaskacephale was a genus of pachycephalosaurid dinosaur that lived in the late Campanian to Maastrichtian stages of the Late Cretaceous ( around 80 to 69 million years ago ) .
Peltandra sagittifolia is a species of plant in the genus Peltandra .
Trixis inula , the tropical threefold , is a plant species native to Texas , Mexico , Central America , northern South America , and the West Indies .
Diuris carinata is a species of orchid , commonly known as the tall bee orchid although members of this genus are generally known as donkey orchids because of the large , ear - like lateral petals .
Nylanderia pubens is a species of ant of the genus Nylanderia , commonly called the Caribbean crazy ant .
Agonum trigeminum is a species of beetle in the Carabidae family that is endemic to the United States .
Heliconia pardoi is a species of plant in the Heliconiaceae family , endemic to Ecuador .
Pyrrharctia is a genus of moths in the Arctiidae family from North and Central America .
Sterculia lychnophora Hance ( Malva nut tree or Taiwan sweet gum tree ) is a species of tree in the genus Sterculia , native to mainland Southeast Asia .
Grindelia nana is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Idaho gumplant and Idaho gumweed .
Orthotylus sicilianus is a species of bug from a family of Miridae that is endemic to Sicily .
Suillia bicolor , is a European species of Heleomyzidae .
Micropterix berytella is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae which is endemic to Israel .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Xenomyxa disseminata .
Barbus multilineatus ( copperstripe barb ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .
Amphisbaena hastata is a worm lizard species in the genus Amphisbaena .
Trifolium friscanum is a rare species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Frisco clover .
Loligo forbesii ( sometimes erroneously spelled forbesi ) , known commonly as the veined squid and long - finned squid , is a commercially important species of squid in the family Loliginidae , the pencil squids .
Haplochromis nigroides is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Kivu on the border of the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Rwanda .
Jefitchia is an extinct genus of prehistoric drum .
Rhipidocladum is a genus of New World woody bamboo in the grass family ) .
Lycium barbarum ( simplified Chinese : 宁夏枸杞 ; traditional Chinese : 寧夏枸杞 ; pinyin : Níngxià gǒuqǐ ) is one of two species of boxthorn in the family Solanaceae from which the goji berry or wolfberry is harvested , the other being Lycium chinense ( Chinese : 枸杞 ; pinyin : gǒuqǐ ) .
Pireneitega pyrenaea is an araneomorph spider species found in Spain and France .
Silgonda rufipes is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Silgonda .
Trioza barrettae is a sap - sucking bug species in the genus Trioza .
Sarcocornia quinqueflora , commonly known as beaded samphire , bead weed , beaded glasswort or glasswort , is a species of succulent halophytic coastal shrub .
Chromis is a genus of fish in the family Pomacentridae .
Coris gaimard , the yellowtail wrasse or African coris , among other vernacular names , is a species of wrasse native to the tropical waters of the central Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean , from Christmas Islands and Cocos Keeling Islands to the Society Islands , Hawaii , and from Japan to Australia .
Sagenosoma is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species , the Elsa Sphinx Moth ( Sagenosoma elsa ) , which is known from the south - western United States ( Arizona , western New Mexico , southern Utah and Colorado ) and northern Mexico .
Katamenes is a genus of potter wasps with species distributed in Europe and Africa .
Syllitus rectus is a species of Cerambycidae that occurs in Australia .
Sisymbrium orientale is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Indian hedgemustard and eastern rocket .
Tragostoma imperator is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tragostoma .
Eulithidium rubrilineatum , common name the red line pheasant , is a species of small sea snail with calcareous opercula , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phasianellidae , the pheasant snails .
Hoplotilapia retrodens is a species of fish endemic to Lake Victoria in East Africa .
Argyrotaenia quadrifasciana , the four - lined leafroller moth , four - banded leafroller or lesser all - green leafroller , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Calyptomyrmex tamil is a species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae , which can be found in Sri Lanka .
Palinurus elephas is a common species of spiny lobster , found in the eastern Atlantic Ocean , from southern Norway to Morocco and the Azores , and in the Mediterranean Sea , except its eastern extremes .
Araucarivora gentilii is a moth in the Elachistidae family , and the only species in the genus Araucarivora .
Roseovarius nubinhibens is a species of Gram - negative , rod - shaped , aerobic dimethylsulfoniopropionate - demethylating bacteria .
Cardiaspina retator is a bug species in the genus Cardiaspina , found on Eucalyptus species in Australia .
Dendragama is a monotypic genus of lizards , containing only the species Dendragama boulengeri , which is commonly called Boulenger 's tree agama and is endemic to Sumatra .
Nothomorphoides irishi is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Nothomorphoides .
Ulopinae is a subfamily of leafhoppers that contains four tribes :
Paedophryne ( from the Ancient Greek paedos ( παίδος ) `` child '' and phryne ( φρύνος ) `` toad , frog '' ) is a genus of microhylid frogs from New Guinea and the nearby D'Entrecasteaux Islands .
Parapteronotus hasemani is a species of ghost knifefish found in the Amazon River Basin in Brazil and Peru .
Clepsis peritana , the garden tortrix or strawberry garden tortrix , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Dalea gattingeri , commonly called Purpletassles or Gattinger Prairie Clover , is a species of flowering plant in the legume family .
Labrisomus fernandezianus is a species of labrisomid blenny endemic to the Juan Fernández Islands , in the southeastern Pacific Ocean .
Cardwellia is a genus of a sole described species of large trees , constituting a part of the plant family Proteaceae .
Cetopsidium morenoi is a species of whale catfish that is found in the central and western portions of the Orinoco River basin in Venezuela and Colombia .
Eburgemellus geminatus is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Eburgemellus .
Orthetrum icteromelas , the spectacled skimmer is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Marasmius sullivantii is a species of fungus in the Marasmiaceae family .
Ischnoptygmatidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Caenogastropoda .
It contains only one species , Randominta meretrix , which is found in the Democratic Republic of Congo .
Cyperus rotundus ( coco - grass , Java grass , nut grass , purple nut sedge or purple nutsedge , red nut sedge , Khmer kravanh chruk ) is a species of sedge ( Cyperaceae ) native to Africa , southern and central Europe ( north to France and Austria ) , and southern Asia .
Halocoryza arenaria is a species of brown coloured ground beetle in the subfamily Scaritinae which was described by Darlington in 1939 .
Claytonia saxosa is a species of wildflower in the purslane family known by the common name Brandegee 's springbeauty .
Gagea bohemica , the Early Star - of - Bethlehem or Radnor Lily is a European and Mediterranean species of flowering plant in the lily family .
Coptosoma is a genus of true bugs belonging to the family Plataspidae , subfamily Platasdinae .
Liolaemus nigromaculatus is a species of tree iguana endemic to the Chilean matorral ecoregionwithin Chile .
Ocoba melanophila is a species of snout moth in the genus Ocoba .
Salix lanata , the woolly willow , is a subarctic species of willow native to Iceland , the Faeroes , northern Scandinavia , Finland , through to eastern Siberia .
Pethia cumingii , known as the Cuming 's barb or the two spot barb ( though that name can also apply to the Ticto barb , P. ticto ) , is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Sri Lanka .
Corythucha arcuata , the oak lace bug is a species of lace bug Tingidae that is a pest of oaks in the Old World .
The Mastacembelidae are a family of fishes , known as the spiny eels .
Pseudis minuta ( common name : lesser swimming frog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Angelica adzharica , the Adjarian angelica is a species of angelica in the carrot family that is endemic to Adjara in Georgia .
Centromochlus is a genus of driftwood catfishes native to South America .
Conus imperialis , common name the imperial cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
It contains the single species Callocosmeta eupicta , which is native to Madagascar .
Allium brevidentatum is a plant species endemic to the Province of Shandong in eastern China .
Atriplex valdesii is a plant species endemic to Mexico .
The Podocarpaceae are a large family of mainly Southern Hemisphere conifers , comprising about 156 species of evergreen trees and shrubs .
Cenangium ferruginosum is a species of fungus which infects young twigs of especially older pines ( Pinus sylvestris ) .
Hydnum ellipsosporum is a species of fungus in the family Hydnaceae that was described from Germany in 2004 .
Cyrenidae is a family of clams in the order Veneroida .
Tyrannomyrmex legatus is a tropical Old World species of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Enchophora sanguinea is a species of lantern bug , a type of hemipteran , found in Central and South America .
Semicassis bisulcata , common name : the Japanese bonnet , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cassidae , the helmet snails and bonnet snails .
Calathus mollis is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found everywhere in Europe except for Albania , Andorra , Finland , Hungary , Italy , Luxembourg , Moldova , Monaco , Russia , San Marino , Slovakia , Switzerland , Vatican City , and various islands .
Lasioglossum clarum , also known as the Lasioglossum ( Ctenomia ) clarum , is a species of bees in the genus Lasioglossum , of the family Halictidae .
Sharks belong to the superorder Selachimorpha in the subclass Elasmobranchii in the class Chondrichthyes .
Acutiramus is an extinct genus of eurypterid which lived in the Late Silurian ( Ludlow ) to Early Devonian .
The wolffish , also known as sea wolves , are a family , Anarhichadidae , of perciform fish .
' Phytolacca sandwicensis , also known as Hawai'i pokeweed , is a member of the Phytolaccaceae family and is a flowering and fruit bearing species endemic to the Hawaiian Islands .
Zoonavena is a genus of swift in the Apodidae family .
The candle tree ( Parmentiera cereifera ) is a species of tree in the family Bignoniaceae .
Lomatium mohavense is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Mojave desertparsley .
Stigmodera cancellata , common name Red Spotted Jewel Beetle , is a species of beetles in the family Buprestidae .
Actia pokharana is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Actia of the family Tachinidae .
Scutellastra longicosta , the long - spined limpet or the duck 's foot limpet , is a species of true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Patellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Selmasaurus is an extinct genus of medium - sized plioplatecarpine mosasaur from the Late Cretaceous of the United States .
Penstemon monoensis is a species of penstemon known by the common name Mono penstemon .
Achelousaurus ( pronunciation : /əˌkiːloʊˈsɔːrəs/ , less commonly : /ˌækᵻˌloʊəˈsɔːrəs/ ; `` Achelous 's lizard '' ) is a genus of centrosaurine ceratopsid dinosaurs from the Late Cretaceous Period of what is now North America , dated to 74.2 million years ago .
Scilla peruviana , the Portuguese squill , is a species of Scilla native to the western Mediterranean region in Iberia , Italy , and northwest Africa .
Persististrombus latus , commonly known as the Bubonian Conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Tetramolopium arenarium is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Maui tetramolopium .
Allium ochotense is a primarily East Asian species of wild onion native to northern Japan , Korea , China , and the Russian Far East , as well as on Attu Island in Alaska .
Colutea arborescens is a species of leguminous shrub known by the common name bladder - senna .
The Dicteriadidae are a small family of damselflies with only two species in two monotypic genera .
It has become commonplace to refer to Borneo elephants as a `` pygmy '' subspecies .
Austromordella verticordiae is a species of beetle in the Austromordella genus .
Flaveria anomala is a Mexican plant species of yellowtops within the sunflower family .
Batozonellus a genus of the spider hunting wasps belonging to the family Pompilidae .
Cordia boissieri is a species of flowering shrub or small tree in the borage family , Boraginaceae .
Dactyloscopus tridigitatus , the Sand stargazer , is a species of sand stargazer native to the Atlantic coasts of the Americas from Florida , USA to Brazil as well as in the Caribbean Ocean and the Gulf of Mexico .
Corynoptera elegans is a species of fungus gnat in the genus Corynoptera found in La Plata , Argentina .
Pseudozorilispe nitida is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudozorilispe .
Clibanarius fonticola is the only species of hermit crab in the world that lives in fresh water .
Baiotomeus is a genus of mammals from the extinct order of Multituberculata .
Peltodytes litoralis is a species of beetle in the genus Peltodytes described in 1912 .
Anthony Kearns ( born 17 August 1971 , Kiltealy , County Wexford , Ireland ) is an internationally - acclaimed tenor , record producer , and a member of The Irish Tenors .
Celestina Boninsegna ( 26 February 1877 -- 14 February 1947 ) was an Italian operatic soprano , known for her interpretations of the heroines in Verdi 's operas .
Irra Petina ( April 18 , 1908 - January 19 , 2000 ) was an actress and singer , as well as a leading contralto with the Metropolitan Opera in New York City .
Tarquinia Tarquini ( 1882 - 25 February 1976 ) was an Italian dramatic soprano and the wife of composer Riccardo Zandonai .
Sergio Franchi ( April 6 , 1926 -- May 1 , 1990 ) , born Sergio Franci Galli , was an Italian - American tenor and actor who enjoyed a meteoric rise to fame in the USA as a multimedia star and recording artist after being discovered on British television in 1962 .
Giuseppe Valdengo ( May 24 , 1914 , Turin -- October 3 , 2007 , Aosta ) was an Italian operatic baritone .
Maria Stader ( November 5 , 1911 -- April 27 , 1999 ) was a Hungarian - born Swiss lyric soprano , known particularly for her Mozart interpretations .
Ruggero Galli was an Italian operatic bass who had an active career during the late 19th and early 20th century .
Tiziana Scandaletti , born in Padua , is an Italian soprano particularly active in chamber music and contemporary classical music .
Robert Merrill ( June 4 , 1917 -- October 23 , 2004 ) was an American operatic baritone and actor , who was also active in the musical theatre circuit .
Sesto Bruscantini ( 10 December 1919 -- 4 May 2003 ) was an Italian baritone , one of the greatest buffo singers of the post - war era , especially renowned in Mozart and Rossini .
Giusto Fernando Tenducci , sometimes called `` il Senesino '' ( ca . 1736 -- 25 January 1790 ) , was a soprano ( castrato ) opera singer and composer , who passed his career partly in Italy but chiefly in Britain .
Maria Murano ( Suzanne Chauvelaud ; July 4 , 1918 in Nogent - sur - Marne -- January 10 , 2009 in Limoges ) was a French lyric mezzo - soprano .
( Philipp ) Eduard Devrient ( 11 August 1801 -- 4 October 1877 ) was a German baritone , librettist , playwright , actor , theatre director , and theatre reformer and historian .
Nicholas Sharratt ( born in Nottingham ) is an English operatic tenor .
Victoria de los Ángeles ( 1 November 1923 -- 15 January 2005 ) was a Spanish operatic lyric coloratura soprano and recitalist whose career began after the Second World War and reached its height in the years from the mid-1950s to the mid-1960s .
Arthur Cosenza ( October 16 , 1924 -- December 27 , 2005 ) was an American impresario , stage director , and baritone of Italian heritage , who was particularly associated with the New Orleans Opera Association .
Alessandra Marianelli ( born 1986 ) is an Italian soprano .
Angiolina Bosio ( 22 August 1830 - 12 April 1859 ) was an Italian operatic soprano who had a major international career from 1846 until her premature death in 1859 at the age of 29 .
Jelena Bodrazic ( born 1971 ) is a mezzo - soprano opera and concert singer born in Backa Palanka , Serbia .
Ludmilla Azova is a soprano opera singer who studied at the New York College of Music and has appeared as a soloist with the New York Philharmonic and the National Orchestra Association , and also performed the role of Fiordiligi in Mozart 's Così fan tutte with the Bermuda Festival Theatre .
Emma Matthews ( born 1970 ) is an English - born Australian lyric coloratura soprano , noted for operatic roles , but also popular on the concert stage .
Beverly Sills ( May 25 , 1929 -- July 2 , 2007 ) was an American operatic soprano whose peak career was between the 1950s and 1970s .
Bessie Abott ( 1878 - February 9 , 1919 ) was an American operatic soprano who had an active international career during the early 20th century .
Josef Greindl ( 23 December 1912 - 16 April 1993 ) was a German operatic bass , remembered mainly for his performances of Wagnerian roles at Bayreuth beginning in 1943 .
Rockland Osgood ( b. February 27 , 1958 , Montgomery , Alabama ) is a contemporary American lyric tenor who has distinguished himself in a wide variety of musical idioms from the Baroque to the latest in Contemporary compositions .
Catherine Malfitano ( born 18 April 1948 ) is an American operatic soprano and opera director .
Joy Clements ( née Joyce Marie Albrecht ; April 29 , 1932 -- October 24 , 2005 ) was an American lyric coloratura soprano who had a substantial opera and concert career from 1956 through the late 1970s .
Kevin Short is an American operatic bass - baritone .
Konrad Jarnot ( born 1972 ) is an English baritone who works in opera and oratorio and is a notable performer of Lieder .
María José Montiel is a mezzo - soprano opera singer born in Madrid .
Armenak Shahmuradyan ( Chah - Mouradian , April 7 , 1878 , Muş , Ottoman Empire -- September 14 , 1939 , Paris ) , also known as the bard of Daron , was an Armenian opera singer ( tenor ) .
Elsie Griffin ( 6 December 1895 -- 21 December 1989 ) was an English opera singer , best known for her performances in the soprano roles of the Savoy Operas with the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company .
Fortunio Bonanova is the pseudonym of Josep Lluís Moll ( January 13 , 1895 in Palma de Mallorca -- April 2 , 1969 in Woodland Hills , California ) , who was a Spanish baritone singer and a film , theater , and television actor .
June Anderson ( born December 30 , 1952 ) is a Grammy Award - winning American coloratura soprano .
Hertha Töpper ( born 19 April 1924 in Graz ) is an Austrian contralto opera singer .
Jean Borthayre ( 25 May 1901 , Musculdy - 25 April 1984 , Montmorency ) was a French operatic baritone , particularly associated with the French and Italian repertories .
Carmela Remigio ( born 1973 in Pescara ) is an Italian lyric soprano singer .
Muriel Costa - Greenspon ( December 1 , 1937 in Detroit , Michigan -- December 26 , 2005 in New York City ) was an American mezzo - soprano who had a lengthy career at the New York City Opera between 1963 - 1993 .
Norma Procter ( born 15 February 1928 in Cleethorpes , Lincolnshire ) is an English contralto who studied with Roy Henderson .
Ernest McChesney ( July 22 , 1912 -- July 25 , 1991 ) was an American tenor who had an active singing career in operas , musicals , and concerts during the late 1920s through the early 1960s .
April Evans is an American soprano who has sung with the Opera Orchestra of New York where she sang Irene in Wagner 's Rienzi in 1983 and with the Teater Kiel in Germany where she was the soprano soloist in Beethoven 's Missa solemnis ( 1986 ) and Rainer Kunad 's Thomas - Evangelium ( 1987 ) .
John Easterlin is an American operatic tenor who has sung at leading opera houses in the United States and internationally , specialising in character and Spieltenor roles .
Dorothee Mields ( born 15 April 1971 ) is a German soprano concert singer of Baroque and contemporary music .
